1
00:00:35,076 --> 00:00:36,036
It looks like she got hit.

2
00:00:36,119 --> 00:00:37,829
<i>There's blood here on her clothes, sir.</i>

3
00:00:39,748 --> 00:00:41,166
<i>We might be able to identify her.</i>

4
00:00:41,249 --> 00:00:44,043
Or maybe we already have
a record on our datebase.

5
00:00:55,138 --> 00:00:58,808
It looks like Carlota has no match here.

6
00:01:02,353 --> 00:01:05,065
<i>We can't underestimate this enemy.</i>

7
00:01:10,320 --> 00:01:11,404
Do you know her?

8
00:01:18,828 --> 00:01:21,081
She does look familiar.

9
00:01:21,164 --> 00:01:23,583
She looks like an actress.

10
00:01:23,666 --> 00:01:25,877
Kim Dominguez.

11
00:01:27,879 --> 00:01:30,715
She looks like a famous actress.
Her name is…

12
00:01:30,799 --> 00:01:31,674
- Kim!
- Kim!

13
00:01:31,758 --> 00:01:32,801
Dominguez.

14
00:01:32,884 --> 00:01:34,093
Santo Domingo!

15
00:01:38,389 --> 00:01:40,391
Kim Santo Domingo.

16
00:01:43,978 --> 00:01:48,733
Viktor sent a red notice to the Moravianos
to hunt her down.

17
00:01:54,697 --> 00:01:58,076
We'll find out where Carlota is
because of her.

18
00:02:04,791 --> 00:02:06,543
I want to finish her off myself.

19
00:02:08,711 --> 00:02:12,173
You know your father's men
already have this covered.

20
00:02:12,257 --> 00:02:13,424
Besides.

21
00:02:13,967 --> 00:02:15,635
You need to rest.

22
00:02:15,718 --> 00:02:17,846
You need to recover.

23
00:02:18,429 --> 00:02:21,224
Because if not, your father
will come after me instead.

24
00:03:56,319 --> 00:03:58,238
- You're so picky!
- Of course.

25
00:04:21,177 --> 00:04:23,888
I've already prepared your room.
You can rest now.

26
00:04:26,849 --> 00:04:28,101
If you don't need anything else.

27
00:04:28,184 --> 00:04:30,937
I'll leave you now so
you can get some rest.

28
00:04:32,730 --> 00:04:33,940
All right.

29
00:04:39,988 --> 00:04:41,197
What do you need, ma'am?

30
00:04:58,047 --> 00:04:59,257
Sianong?

31
00:05:07,140 --> 00:05:08,224
Let's meet.

32
00:05:08,891 --> 00:05:10,351
I need your help.

33
00:05:17,442 --> 00:05:18,526
Are you expecting someone?

34
00:05:19,193 --> 00:05:20,278
No one.

35
00:05:21,070 --> 00:05:22,405
Chiara is in Prague.

36
00:05:24,741 --> 00:05:26,242
Looks like you have a visitor.

37
00:05:26,909 --> 00:05:28,036
Okay.

38
00:05:35,918 --> 00:05:36,919
Don't!

39
00:05:37,754 --> 00:05:39,255
What's going on?

40
00:05:39,338 --> 00:05:40,965
Why do you have guns?

41
00:05:44,093 --> 00:05:46,387
Why do you have guns?

42
00:05:50,933 --> 00:05:52,268
Just Sianong?

43
00:05:53,186 --> 00:05:55,021
You don't know his last name?

44
00:05:58,858 --> 00:06:00,526
But he's Mikoy's friend.

45
00:06:00,610 --> 00:06:03,446
Do you remember the shape of his face?

46
00:06:07,408 --> 00:06:08,367
Yes.

47
00:06:08,868 --> 00:06:12,163
Just describe it
so we can get a clearer picture.

48
00:06:12,246 --> 00:06:13,206
Okay.

49
00:06:29,097 --> 00:06:31,224
He has a pointed nose, straight.

50
00:06:31,307 --> 00:06:34,519
With big eyes
but they're slightly round almond-shaped.

51
00:06:34,602 --> 00:06:36,312
Thick eyebrows.

52
00:06:36,395 --> 00:06:37,897
Hair is thick.

53
00:06:37,980 --> 00:06:40,983
His hair is dark brown to black.

54
00:06:44,695 --> 00:06:47,532
And, where was it again.

55
00:06:47,615 --> 00:06:50,493
He has a mole on his left cheek.

56
00:06:50,576 --> 00:06:52,954
- Yes, left cheek.
- Okay.

57
00:06:56,249 --> 00:06:57,959
- Really?
- Yes, ma'am.

58
00:07:07,552 --> 00:07:09,720
I'm not a cartographic artist.

59
00:07:13,891 --> 00:07:14,851
What's that?

60
00:07:14,934 --> 00:07:16,978
I just want to know if Sianong works

61
00:07:17,061 --> 00:07:19,897
for that Global Agency
for Government Operations.

62
00:07:21,190 --> 00:07:23,401
Why didn't you say sooner?

63
00:07:25,153 --> 00:07:26,362
Why?

64
00:07:26,446 --> 00:07:29,407
You can hack
the personal files of that agency?

65
00:07:29,490 --> 00:07:31,284
That's basic for me.

66
00:07:31,367 --> 00:07:34,287
I actually have a better idea
for us to find out

67
00:07:34,370 --> 00:07:38,082
if Sianong really works for that agency.

68
00:07:44,922 --> 00:07:46,090
What happened?

69
00:07:46,716 --> 00:07:48,926
Dad, why are you here?

70
00:07:49,677 --> 00:07:52,763
Bro, why do you have guns?

71
00:07:55,641 --> 00:07:57,768
It's better if you don't know
anything yet.

72
00:08:02,482 --> 00:08:04,442
Is this about the Valtrovis?

73
00:08:05,026 --> 00:08:08,738
Is this about Sis Chiara's family
being a syndicate?

74
00:08:09,780 --> 00:08:11,449
Wait, how did you know that?

75
00:08:11,532 --> 00:08:13,326
I knew about it for a while now.

76
00:08:14,327 --> 00:08:16,245
Dad just didn't want me to say it.

77
00:08:19,832 --> 00:08:21,751
But still, how did you find out?

78
00:08:22,335 --> 00:08:24,337
My friend's dad told her.

79
00:08:24,420 --> 00:08:25,796
His dad is a police officer.

80
00:08:25,880 --> 00:08:28,132
Who's investigating the Valtrovis.

81
00:08:30,134 --> 00:08:31,135
The question is…

82
00:08:33,387 --> 00:08:34,597
just a friend?

83
00:08:36,432 --> 00:08:38,559
Or a girlfriend?

84
00:08:39,560 --> 00:08:40,686
- Dad.
- Dad.

85
00:08:41,938 --> 00:08:42,939
You, really!

86
00:08:43,523 --> 00:08:44,690
You two…

87
00:08:45,233 --> 00:08:46,609
I'm just joking.

88
00:08:48,528 --> 00:08:51,948
But, Bro, I saw…

89
00:08:52,532 --> 00:08:53,616
Sir Kian earlier.

90
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:56,786
At school earlier, so I remembered you.

91
00:08:58,412 --> 00:09:00,039
I have a bad feeling.

92
00:09:01,749 --> 00:09:05,545
I feel like something bad
is going to happen.

93
00:09:11,801 --> 00:09:16,430
They think our law enforcement
here in the Philippines is sophisticated.

94
00:09:16,514 --> 00:09:18,099
What they don't know is

95
00:09:18,182 --> 00:09:20,685
our setup here is actually very simple.

96
00:09:20,768 --> 00:09:24,272
And you don't need
a sophisticated hacking system

97
00:09:24,355 --> 00:09:27,650
for us to identify their personnel.

98
00:09:32,363 --> 00:09:35,366
Everything here is very simple.

99
00:09:37,660 --> 00:09:38,744
So how?

100
00:09:39,328 --> 00:09:42,456
You just need to know
their social media account.

101
00:09:42,540 --> 00:09:45,376
Like Fishbook.

102
00:09:49,922 --> 00:09:51,048
Then.

103
00:09:51,674 --> 00:09:54,802
We'll go to their Christmas party.

104
00:10:00,391 --> 00:10:02,560
If Sianong is really there,

105
00:10:03,728 --> 00:10:05,438
I'm sure you'll recognize him

106
00:10:05,521 --> 00:10:07,857
once we scroll
through the pictures, right?

107
00:10:07,940 --> 00:10:12,653
We'll find out if he really works
for that agency.

108
00:10:38,679 --> 00:10:42,141
Looks like him and Alex

109
00:10:42,683 --> 00:10:45,978
are agents working against us.

110
00:10:53,027 --> 00:10:54,236
Do you know them?

111
00:11:05,414 --> 00:11:07,041
Your concern is valid.

112
00:11:07,124 --> 00:11:09,585
Because it looks like
the police are targeting them.

113
00:11:26,769 --> 00:11:29,438
You know, I'm starting to like you.

114
00:11:30,856 --> 00:11:32,441
Looks like you were right.

115
00:11:34,902 --> 00:11:37,321
You could actually be a reliable partner.

116
00:11:37,405 --> 00:11:38,739
I need someone like you

117
00:11:38,823 --> 00:11:42,326
to navigate the intricacies of life
here in the Philippines.

118
00:11:42,952 --> 00:11:44,078
The question is…

119
00:11:46,205 --> 00:11:48,249
can I trust you?

120
00:11:49,208 --> 00:11:50,584
Of course.

121
00:11:54,463 --> 00:11:57,258
You know the one thing
that's very important to me?

122
00:12:08,352 --> 00:12:09,353
And you know that.

123
00:12:10,938 --> 00:12:12,189
Very well.

124
00:12:15,067 --> 00:12:20,823
So let me share something
very personal with you as well.

125
00:12:30,499 --> 00:12:34,920
I love Mikoy D. Pinagpala very much.

126
00:12:37,089 --> 00:12:38,466
<i>How do I know?</i>

127
00:12:45,264 --> 00:12:48,601
<i>We just made the definition</i>
<i>of love more complicated.</i>

128
00:12:54,315 --> 00:12:57,943
<i>And I realized that I really</i>
<i>have fallen for Mikoy.</i>

129
00:13:09,413 --> 00:13:13,959
And every time I remember that dream,

130
00:13:16,212 --> 00:13:17,796
my heart skips a beat.

131
00:13:19,006 --> 00:13:24,220
<i>And I'm filled with excitement</i>
<i>and overwhelming happiness.</i>

132
00:13:24,887 --> 00:13:26,472
<i>And suddenly,</i>

133
00:13:27,806 --> 00:13:30,643
<i>I can't wait for tomorrow anymore.</i>

134
00:13:31,936 --> 00:13:33,479
<i>Because I know</i>

135
00:13:34,021 --> 00:13:36,815
<i>that tomorrow,</i>

136
00:13:36,899 --> 00:13:39,318
<i>I'll get to spend it with him.</i>

137
00:14:18,649 --> 00:14:20,568
Why would you say that?

138
00:14:49,972 --> 00:14:54,101
Angelito, what we're about to tell you
is important.

139
00:14:55,269 --> 00:14:56,353
So listen carefully.

140
00:14:59,523 --> 00:15:00,733
This is serious.

141
00:15:11,035 --> 00:15:13,454
I'm working as an asset
for the government.

142
00:15:17,750 --> 00:15:21,253
The syndicate that's suspected
to be run by the Valtrovis.

143
00:15:51,408 --> 00:15:52,785
That's her car.

144
00:15:52,868 --> 00:15:54,161
Park over there.

145
00:16:16,058 --> 00:16:17,059
Clear here too.

146
00:16:47,715 --> 00:16:49,258
So my suspicion was right.

147
00:16:54,930 --> 00:16:57,599
I just didn't expect it would
happen to me too.

148
00:17:09,111 --> 00:17:14,408
But first, start by giving me information
that I can use against them.

149
00:17:14,491 --> 00:17:17,911
Before I talk, I want something in return.

150
00:17:32,468 --> 00:17:34,678
You've broken plenty of laws too.

151
00:17:42,436 --> 00:17:44,438
More like a saint with horns.

152
00:17:44,521 --> 00:17:46,398
Maybe you forgot,

153
00:17:46,482 --> 00:17:48,150
you tried to kill me.

154
00:17:51,403 --> 00:17:52,613
Just like you.

155
00:17:54,073 --> 00:17:56,283
But it depends on the information
you'll give me.

156
00:17:56,867 --> 00:18:00,245
If it's something useful that
I can use against the Moravianos,

157
00:18:01,371 --> 00:18:03,082
maybe we can work something out.

158
00:18:04,541 --> 00:18:05,876
I know a lot.

159
00:18:06,585 --> 00:18:09,088
We can start with how Viktor took

160
00:18:09,171 --> 00:18:12,508
the throne of the Moraviano syndicate.

161
00:18:13,133 --> 00:18:15,969
Viktor wasn't favored
in the world of the Mafia.

162
00:19:20,159 --> 00:19:21,618
<i>La Morte Bianca.</i>

163
00:19:23,912 --> 00:19:27,124
<i>She was the one who gave Viktor</i>
<i>his newfound power.</i>

164
00:19:34,548 --> 00:19:38,594
<i>La Morte Bianca didn't just</i>
<i>protect the Valtrovis.</i>

165
00:19:48,979 --> 00:19:51,398
I'm grateful for your history lesson.

166
00:19:52,065 --> 00:19:53,692
But that's not what I need.

167
00:19:53,775 --> 00:19:55,944
Not a single thing in your story
gave me information

168
00:19:56,028 --> 00:19:58,822
about how to take down the Moravianos.

169
00:20:04,953 --> 00:20:08,040
You sounded so confident earlier
you said you knew a lot.

170
00:20:08,749 --> 00:20:13,045
And now you're telling me
you don't have all the answers?

171
00:20:13,629 --> 00:20:17,007
I know someone who has
the answers you're looking for.

172
00:20:17,090 --> 00:20:18,675
Doesn't it make you wonder?

173
00:20:18,759 --> 00:20:22,012
What Viktor gave La Morte Bianca

174
00:20:22,095 --> 00:20:25,182
in exchange
for all that protection and power?

175
00:20:30,187 --> 00:20:31,855
<i>In the world of the mafia</i>

176
00:20:32,731 --> 00:20:34,483
<i>it's always about blood.</i>

177
00:20:41,615 --> 00:20:42,908
Chiara.

178
00:23:08,386 --> 00:23:10,180
<i>La Fornarina.</i>

179
00:23:12,516 --> 00:23:14,601
<i>Chiara Valtrovi.</i>

180
00:23:23,610 --> 00:23:26,571
How can you be so sure
that Chiara is La Fornarina?

181
00:23:31,618 --> 00:23:35,705
And I can see in your eyes
that you believe what I'm saying.

182
00:23:36,665 --> 00:23:40,544
I can't just believe words alone
especially coming from you.

183
00:24:06,903 --> 00:24:08,530
I was right all along.

184
00:24:18,707 --> 00:24:21,877
Viktor didn't believe me at first.

185
00:24:22,460 --> 00:24:23,795
Turns out I was right.

186
00:24:24,754 --> 00:24:26,631
What do you mean?

187
00:24:26,715 --> 00:24:30,468
My initial report to Viktor
was that Mikoy is a spy.

188
00:24:31,720 --> 00:24:34,514
He's working with police
officers like you.

189
00:24:34,598 --> 00:24:35,807
What?

190
00:24:41,479 --> 00:24:45,192
Sooner or later, he'll find out
that the two of you are connected.

191
00:24:46,651 --> 00:24:48,653
And when that happens,

192
00:24:49,696 --> 00:24:52,240
Mikoy will be dead.

193
00:25:06,713 --> 00:25:07,839
Ma'am.

194
00:25:13,303 --> 00:25:16,598
I know I'm not in the position
to say this, but

195
00:25:17,515 --> 00:25:18,475
Mikoy,

196
00:25:18,975 --> 00:25:21,269
being friends with a police agent,

197
00:25:21,353 --> 00:25:22,771
is not definitive.

198
00:25:29,694 --> 00:25:31,905
Believe it or not, ma'am.

199
00:25:31,988 --> 00:25:34,741
I'm the last person who would fool you.

200
00:25:35,617 --> 00:25:38,161
All I'm saying is, you're right.

201
00:25:40,747 --> 00:25:43,833
Love is giving someone a chance
to explain themselves.

202
00:25:45,001 --> 00:25:47,462
You probably have nothing to lose
if you hear his reason about

203
00:25:47,545 --> 00:25:50,757
why he did the things he did, right?

204
00:25:52,092 --> 00:25:53,760
Like John Lloyd said,

205
00:25:54,511 --> 00:25:56,137
or was it Papa Piolo?

206
00:26:16,241 --> 00:26:17,450
It's Alex.

207
00:26:17,534 --> 00:26:18,952
The agent handling me.

208
00:26:19,953 --> 00:26:23,331
But she specifically told me
to never answer this phone

209
00:26:23,415 --> 00:26:25,542
until she was sure it was safe.

210
00:26:26,126 --> 00:26:27,544
And now she's calling herself.

211
00:26:28,545 --> 00:26:29,754
That can only mean one thing,

212
00:26:29,838 --> 00:26:32,340
something bad happened.

213
00:26:34,009 --> 00:26:35,218
What are you waiting for?

214
00:26:35,802 --> 00:26:36,928
Answer it.

215
00:26:39,556 --> 00:26:41,099
Mikoy's phone is active.

216
00:26:43,601 --> 00:26:44,686
Do you want me to kill it?

217
00:26:44,769 --> 00:26:45,687
No.

218
00:26:50,275 --> 00:26:51,776
You said it yourself.

219
00:26:57,741 --> 00:27:01,619
So maybe this is
the answers to my questions, right?

220
00:27:03,121 --> 00:27:04,331
Yes.

221
00:27:14,674 --> 00:27:15,842
Why are you calling?

222
00:27:15,925 --> 00:27:19,137
<i>Didn't you say</i>
<i>I shouldn't answer this phone?</i>

223
00:27:19,220 --> 00:27:21,806
This is urgent and I need
to talk to you right away.

224
00:27:22,390 --> 00:27:24,100
Why? What's wrong?

225
00:27:24,184 --> 00:27:25,977
Mikoy, listen to me carefully.

226
00:27:26,061 --> 00:27:27,562
You need to stay away from Chiara.

227
00:27:29,397 --> 00:27:31,274
Wait, what are you talking about?

228
00:27:31,983 --> 00:27:33,109
What do you mean in danger?

229
00:28:03,098 --> 00:28:04,766
- Your brother…
- I understand, Dad.

230
00:28:04,849 --> 00:28:07,644
No one should know about
this, not even your mother!

231
00:28:07,727 --> 00:28:09,604
I'm the one who decided
to get into this mess.

232
00:28:09,687 --> 00:28:13,233
<i>So I hope you will trust me</i>
<i>that I can stand by this decision.</i>

233
00:28:13,316 --> 00:28:14,609
<i>And about Mom,</i>

234
00:28:14,692 --> 00:28:16,653
<i>if there's something</i>
<i>bad that will happen to me,</i>

235
00:28:16,736 --> 00:28:19,364
at least I know the two of you
are there for her.

236
00:28:19,447 --> 00:28:20,698
<i>The agent escaped from us.</i>

237
00:28:20,782 --> 00:28:21,950
You all are stupid!

238
00:28:30,458 --> 00:28:35,296
<i>I will make sure that</i>
<i>everyone who betrayed me will pay!</i>
